title: Morse 2-5 After School Childcare Program
body: Our after-school program is designed to build children’s social skills and enhance their school-day learning. Children engage in developmentally appropriate project-based learning curriculum, both individually and in groups.

title: U10 League, Monday/Thursday
body: The U10 League is for 3rd and 4th graders. The league helps develop sportsmanship, teamwork, and discipline. Individual teams will establish their own practice schedules in addition to the two weekly games.

title: Cambridge Youth Soccer In-Town
body: CYS In-Town program is for 1st – 8th graders. The game format ranges from 4v4 at the young end to 8v8 for the oldest players. Games are played on Saturdays within Cambridge. 3rd grade and older teams also practice once per week, a second practice is optional.
